Reproduction of ATAG Waypoint scenarios in AeroMAPS

Four scenarios are presented:
-S0: baseline / continuation of current trends
-S1: pushing technology and operations
-S2: aggressive sustainable fuel deployment
-S3: aspirational and aggressive technology perspective

Each scenario is generated using different assumptions regarding 5 dimensions: traffic, technology, operations, offsets,
and SAF. However assumptions are not always quantified in the ATAG report, meaning we have to complete them with
AeroMAPS inputs.

-Traffic        : Fixed growth rates per period, values taken from report (p. 31)
-Technology     : Baseline annual improvements taken from report (p. 40), incremental technologies estimated from figure
                (p. 41)
-Operations     : Annual operational improvements (p. 60) and load factor (p . 61) estimated from figures
-Offsets        : Modeled in AeroMAPS to cap 2019 emissions until 2035 than decline linearly to zero
-SAF            : SAF quantities estimated from figures (p. 79) with extra assumptions on how quantities are split among
                pathways. Top-down pathways costs are assumed as exogenous inputs based on figure (p. 84). Lifecycle
                emissions, efficiencies, economics completed with values from Yang 2025
                (https://doi.org/10.1016/j.resconrec.2025.108124) and CORSIA LCA supporting document
                (https://www.icao.int/sites/default/files/environmental-protection/CORSIA/Documents/SCS-Evaluation/
                CORSIA_Supporting_Document_CORSIA-Eligible-Fuels_LCA_Methodology_V6.pdf)
    -HEFA                   : production split 2/2 into HEFA waste/residues and HEFA oil crops
    -Advanced feedstocks    : production split 4/4 into ATJ cellulosic crops, ATJ agricultural residues, FT woody
                            biomass, FT MSW
    -Waste gas              : ATJ industrial waste gas
    -Power to liquid        : PtL


Besides the standard scenarios and assumptions from ATAG scenarios, variant scenarios are also explored:
-Traffic        : standard scenarios are explored with central air traffic growth, but extra variants are explored with
                low and high growth scenarios

-Scope          : AeroMAPS emissions considers a Well-to-Wake (WTW) scope, while ATAG considers a Tank-to-Wake (TTW)
                scope, a TTW variant is therefore included considering only kerosene combustion emissions (no lifecycle
                approach) and SAF emissions are based on a percentual emissions reductions from the TTW kerosene (p. 57
                fueling net zero report). However, 73.8 gCO2/MJ is considered for kerosene combustion (value from
                https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-022-35392-1) instead of the 71.82 gCO2/MJ as in the ATAG report (p. 100)

-Technology     : T1-T5 variants varying only technology levers (no SAF, operations, offsets).
    -T1 baseline        : 0.2% annual improvement
    -T2 conservative    : 0.2% 2019-2035, 0.4% 2035-2050
    -T3 new configs     : 0.2% 2019-2035, 0.5% 2035-2050
    -T4 electrification : T3 + electric aircraft below 100 seats by 2040 (2% energy demand by 2050)
    -T5 aspirational    : T4 + hydrogen 100-200 seats by 2035 (20% energy demand by 2050)
